body:
The most-loved n8n flow on our team has 7 lines of custom code in it. That's it.

Function node:

const meeting = $input.item.json.meeting_notes;

const summary = await callClaude(`Summarise this customer meeting in 3 bullets, all action items separately. No marketing language. ${meeting}`);

const actions = summary.actions || [];

for (const action of actions) {

  await createHubSpotTask(action.owner, action.text, action.due);

}

return summary;

What it does:

→ Reads meeting notes from Notion (when an AE pastes them in)

→ Sends to Claude for summary + action extraction

→ Creates HubSpot tasks with owners and due dates

→ Posts the summary to a Slack thread

Why AEs love it: the action items get assigned automatically. They never have to remember.

7 lines of code. ~6 hours/week saved across a 5-person sales team.

Most leverage in B2B GTM automation isn't in big platforms. It's in tiny, specific flows that remove a single point of friction.

#n8n #Claude #RevOps #MarketingAutomation
